    "message": "Operation 'getRandomAvatar' has semantic quality issues: vague_summary, missing_input_details, missing_output_details, missing_context. The current summary and description lack specificity about the API's purpose (CC0 placeholder avatars) and don't adequately explain inputs, outputs, or behavior. The description doesn't mention what parameters are available, what format the response is in, or that each request generates a different avatar. An AI agent needs to understand that this generates random avatars for placeholder purposes, what customization options exist, and that the response is an image file. The improved version adds domain context (CC0 placeholder), clarifies the response type (image file), mentions parameter customization, and explains the randomization behavior.",
